videos.description: Daxter Miles Jr. gets the steal and passes to Jevon Carter who drains the 3-pointer.
videos.headline: West Virginia turns steal into Carter 3-pointer

videos.description: Jontay Porter jumps, blocks the 3-point attempt by Chase Harler, then Porter runs the floor and makes his own 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Missouri's Porter blocks 3-pointer and then makes his own

videos.description: Jeremiah Tilmon fights through the contact to make the shot plus the foul.
videos.headline: Missouri's Tilmon makes the and-1 shot

videos.description: Daxter Miles Jr. gets the steal and goes the length of the court to score to cut Missouri's lead to 1.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Miles gets steal and makes the layup

videos.description: Jevon Carter pulls up and hits the 3-pointer to give West Virginia their first lead since 24-23.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Carter hits 3-pointer late to take the lead

videos.description: Bob Huggins credits the comeback to Jevon Carter and Daxter Miles Jr. as West Virginia defeats Missouri 83-79.
videos.headline: Huggins credits Carter and Miles for leading West Virginia's comeback
